parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at low speeds. This can lead to accidents, loss of control, and injuries.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault message appears on the instrument panel
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle vibrates abnormally
the steering wheel jerks to one side
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
and the power steering assist light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
stalls
or jerks while driving
the "wrench" warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle idles roughly
and the accelerator pedal becomes unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission fluid leak can cause the transmission to fail, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fluid leaks from the left-hand half-shaft seal
the vehicle surges or jerks while driving
and the transmission fluid level is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body/throttle actuator can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge, leading to a loss of control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or surges while driving
the "tool" or "wrench" light illuminates on the dashboard
the engine fails to respond to the throttle
the vehicle coasts to a stop
and the accelerator pedal may feel soft or unresponsive.
